Then access them for the drivers/software.Simple forward and backward, system restores or installs. Secondly, have all motherboards require a direct solid state drive for just Windows operating systems to be flashed too. Basically like an XBOX. Windows would be protected from viruses by a simple program that monitors the file structure of the main ss hdd drive. If files are modified. The next reboot, sets the files back to factory. All hidden drives of course. Except via command prompt or even a certified installer accessible, for driver / software updates.Lastly Windows, by default. Monster powered isolation technology cut unwanted external noise, so all you hear is the music.What are OEM products???OEM (original equipment manufacturer) refers to companies that originally make the products for others to repackage and sell(say for example an outsourcing company in China). Resellers(like Beats™ & Monster™) buy OEM products in bulk, minus the costly retail packaging that comes with individually sold units. The product itself is essentially THE SAME as its more expensive, retail-packaged sibling.In short, OEMs are basically the same with their original counterparts - same sound quality, same process but not the same price. The relatively BIIIIGGGG difference with the price comes with those costly product advertising, fancy packaging, add-on materials(cds&manuals), shop rent, etc.So what would you choose?
